<plot>This tv movie features two stories by qv##nm0785245##, who also wrote the stories of the original qv##tt0052520## series. "The Theater": A young girl goes to the cinema to see qv##tt0032599## with qv##nm0000026##. Suddenly she sees scenes from her own life instead of the comedy. The scenes actually took place earlier that day. She is very confused because the other people didn't see those scenes. As she goes to see the movie again, scenes from her future appear on the screen. And that future is very frightening... "Where the Dead Are": Dr. Benjamin Ramsey is professor at the university in Boston in 1868. In front of his students he performes an appendix operation. As the patient O'Neil dies after the operation, Dr. Ramsey discovers that O'Neil suffered from a serious scull fracture twelve years ago. Since no one could have survived such an injury, he travels to the mysterious island where O'Neil came from. There he visits Dr. Jeremy Wheaton who earlier had experimented with tissue regeneration...</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?621976</url></doc>
